const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What Hestan appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "Hestan's residential lineup, primarily cooking and outdoor. Indoor: KRD freestanding dual-fuel ranges (KRD304, KRD365, KRD485GD), KRG freestanding gas ranges (KRG304, KRG365), KRT gas rangetops (KRT365, KRT484GD, KRT485GD), KRTI induction rangetops (KRTI36), KDO wall ovens (KDO30 with TwinVection dual convection), select integrated refrigeration columns. Outdoor: GABR / GMBR / GSBR built-in grills, GRFR24 outdoor fridge / freezer combos, GRSR24 single-zone outdoor refrigerators, GRSL24 left-hinged variants, GRWG24 dual-zone with wine storage. Hestan residential focuses on cooking and outdoor — there's no Hestan laundry and no Hestan dishwasher line. We work the residential consumer lineup that launched in 2018 (indoor) and 2016 (outdoor)."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Hestan repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. Hestan repair pricing sits in the upper-luxury tier — comparable to Wolf or Thermador, reflecting Anaheim CA-based parts supply (35 miles from our West Hollywood dispatch). Common Hestan service items: spark electrode $185-$285 per burner (the most common rangetop service item on KRT series); spark module $265-$405; KDO wall oven TwinVection convection fan motor $345-$525 per fan (KDO has dual fans); oven thermostat $265-$405; bake / broil element $245-$385; smart-control board $385-$580 (Hestan's connected platform runs a more sophisticated control than competing luxury ranges); door hinge $345-$525; glass touch panel $485-$780. Outdoor side: GRFR24 / GRSR24 compressor work $585-$985, outdoor grill igniter on GABR / GMBR / GSBR $245-$385 (weather-rated, heavier spec than indoor). Parts ship from Anaheim — typically 2-5 day lead, the shortest pipeline of any luxury brand we cover."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the most common Hestan failure pattern we see?",
    a: "The patterns are still emerging because the indoor residential lineup is young — launched 2018, so 8-year max service window in 2026. What we're seeing in the current LA service mix: <strong>CircuFlame center-burner spark electrode wear</strong> on KRT and KRD ranges (the high-BTU center burner erodes its electrode faster than the surrounding lower-BTU zones, $245 typical fix); <strong>smart-platform connectivity drops</strong> (app pairing failures, firmware version conflicts, control board work — 15-20% of our Hestan calls touch the connected platform in some way); <strong>KDO wall oven TwinVection fan motor service</strong> on early-cohort KDO30 units ($345-$525 per fan motor; KDO uses dual convection fans, both can wear); and on the outdoor side, <strong>GRSR / GRFR evaporator fan service</strong> driven by inland-summer ambient temps in Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and Bel Air pool-deck installs. We won't claim a 15-year wear curve on equipment that hasn't been in the field 15 years — patterns we refine as the install base ages."
  },
  {
    q: "How does Hestan compare to Wolf?",
    a: "Honest comparison from servicing both regularly: Hestan and Wolf compete at the same price tier and similar build-quality philosophy, but they're different products. <strong>Wolf</strong> is sealed-burner sealed-system construction (Sub-Zero Group, Madison WI), dominant US distribution through authorized dealers, factory service network with cross-country reach, parts ship from Madison via Sub-Zero's well-developed pipeline (typical 3-7 day). The Wolf service economics are well-understood — repair costs are predictable, parts are available, technicians trained on Wolf are common. <strong>Hestan</strong> is newer (residential indoor lineup since 2018), smaller dealer network, smart-cooking platform built around connected-app control, Anaheim CA construction with parts supply 35 miles from West Hollywood (2-5 day typical). Repair costs run roughly comparable to Wolf at the major-component level; the smart-platform electronics on Hestan add a cost tier Wolf doesn't have because Wolf's controls are simpler and more mechanical. The Hestan installations we see in Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and the design-forward LA neighborhoods were chosen specifically because the owner wanted something other than the default luxury brand — Hestan's smaller market share is part of why owners chose it."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do Hestan appliances last?",
    a: "Hestan's design target is 20-25 year service life with normal use — comparable to Wolf, Sub-Zero, and Thermador on durability targets. Cast iron grates, brass sealed burners, diamond burner bowls, all-stainless construction, Anaheim CA factory build. The lineup is too young to confirm those targets empirically (residential indoor since 2018 = 8 years max in the field), but the construction tier is consistent with multi-decade ranges we service from other premium brands. What we are seeing in early cohorts: spark electrodes on CircuFlame center burners ($245-$285), KDO TwinVection fan motors on early units ($345-$525 per fan), smart-control boards on the very earliest 2018-2019 units entering replacement cycles ($385-$580). Cost-of-ownership is favorable: against $9,000-$18,000 replacement-unit pricing for new Hestan ranges (depending on configuration), a $300-$600 mid-life repair recovers years of service. Custom-finish installations specifically favor repair over replacement — Hestan's color and trim options change between model years and exact-match replacement isn't always available."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Hestan made in the USA?",
    a: "Yes. Hestan residential appliances are designed and manufactured in California — the 130,000 sq ft Anaheim facility at 3375 E La Palma Avenue houses the parent Hestan Commercial Corporation (founded 2013 by Stanley Cheng, also founder of Meyer Corporation — the parent of Anolon, Circulon, and Farberware cookware). Hestan Commercial launched outdoor residential in 2016 and indoor residential in 2018; both lines are still manufactured in Anaheim. Parts ship from US distribution rather than European supply chains, which translates to 2-5 day typical lead time for OEM parts on our service calls — faster than ILVE or Bertazzoni (12-21 day European), comparable to Thermador via BSH Irvine (1-2 day), and the shortest pipeline of any luxury brand we cover. The American-made positioning is part of why some customers choose Hestan over Italian or German alternatives — and it's relevant to service economics, since parts don't carry the multi-week European-import wait."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find the official Hestan manual or warranty information?",
    a: `Our technicians work independently of Hestan's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day across Southern California.`
  }
];

