<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Hestan is the newest luxury brand on our service list — Anaheim CA manufactured, indoor residential lineup launched 2018 — we see them in Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and Beverly Hills kitchens where the owner wanted something nobody else has, manufactured 35 miles from our dispatch.</h2>

    <p>Hestan's indoor residential lineup launched in 2018 as the home-cooking arm of Hestan Commercial Corporation, an Anaheim-based manufacturer founded in 2013 by Stanley Cheng — also the founder of Meyer Corporation, the parent of Anolon, Circulon, and Farberware cookware. Hestan's outdoor cooking and refrigeration lineup launched in 2016, two years before the indoor side. In our 5-county SoCal service mix, Hestan shows up in a specific demographic: Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and Sherman Oaks design-forward kitchens where the homeowner specifically wanted something other than the default Wolf or Thermador, plus the wealthier eastside neighborhoods (Los Feliz, Hancock Park, Larchmont) and the premium Westside corridor (Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Brentwood) where the smart-platform integration or the American-made positioning was the deciding spec.</p>

    <p>Three Hestan-specific realities shape every service call. First, <strong>this is not a full-suite brand</strong>. Hestan residential covers cooking (KRD freestanding dual-fuel ranges, KRG freestanding gas ranges, KRT and KRTI rangetops, KDO wall ovens), select integrated refrigeration, ventilation, and the full outdoor cooking + refrigeration suite (GABR / GMBR / GSBR built-in grills, GRSR / GRFR / GRWG outdoor refrigerators). There's no Hestan laundry. There's no Hestan dishwasher line — when we see a Hestan kitchen, the dishwasher in the same room is almost always Miele, Bosch, or KitchenAid. Owners scope kitchen suites accordingly. Second, <strong>the smart-platform electronics add a service category competitors don't have</strong>. Hestan's connected app integration runs through a more sophisticated control board than Wolf or Thermador's relatively simple electronics — connectivity issues (app pairing, firmware updates, control board work) come up across our Hestan service mix. The platform is the brand's selling point and also its newest service variable. Third, <strong>parts ship from Anaheim — about 35 miles from our West Hollywood dispatch</strong>, typical 2-5 day lead time. This is the shortest parts pipeline of any luxury brand we cover: Italian-origin brands (ILVE, Bertazzoni) carry 12-21 day European-supply waits; Wolf and Sub-Zero ship from Madison WI (3-7 day); Hestan is local.</p>

    <p>Every Hestan service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM Hestan parts, and an honest written quote before any work begins. The indoor residential lineup is young — eight years in the field as of 2026 — so we frame service patterns honestly: early-adopter cohorts are starting to come back for service now, but we won't invent 15-year wear curves on equipment that hasn't been around 15 years. We hold common KRT / KRD spark electrodes, oven igniters, and KDO convection fan motors on the truck for the dominant 30 and 36-inch configurations.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 01b WHY HESTAN IS DIFFERENT -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01b, The local angle</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Why Hestan service works different in LA than any other luxury brand we cover.</h2>

    <p>Hestan is the only luxury appliance brand on our service list that's manufactured locally. The 130,000 sq ft Anaheim facility on East La Palma Avenue is where the KRD ranges, KRT rangetops, KDO wall ovens, and GRFR / GRSR outdoor refrigerators are manufactured — 35 miles from our West Hollywood dispatch. Every other premium brand we service ships parts from somewhere harder: Wolf and Sub-Zero from Madison WI (3-7 day lead), Thermador from BSH's Irvine CA distribution (1-2 day, the next-closest premium pipeline), Miele from Princeton NJ (5-10 day), ILVE and Bertazzoni from Italy (14-21 day European supply). Hestan parts arrive on our truck in 2-5 days — sometimes same-day when the warehouse has stock.</p>

    <p>That short pipeline matters more than people realize. A KRT365 spark module that takes 3 days from Anaheim doesn't disrupt anyone's kitchen the way a 14-day Italian wait does. For the customer, that's faster recovery and less downtime — sometimes a same-day fix when parts are already in our Anaheim warehouse.</p>

    <p>There's a sentiment angle too. The owner of Hestan Commercial Corporation, Stanley Cheng, also founded Meyer Corporation — the parent company of Anolon, Circulon, and Farberware cookware. Most of our Hestan customers in Beverly Hills, Bel Air, and Calabasas already have the cookware in their kitchens before they buy the appliances. The brand-to-cookware continuity is part of why Hestan made it into these households at all. Jan Heck was appointed CEO of Hestan Commercial in 2025, succeeding Eric Deng — service-network investment has accelerated under the new leadership, including stronger authorized-dealer training and OEM parts distribution to independent service companies.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 CATEGORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Hestan repair categories</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Indoor cooking, outdoor cooking, ventilation, refrigeration.</h2>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>Hestan's indoor residential lineup is young — service patterns are still emerging</h3>
      <p>Hestan's residential indoor cooking line launched in 2018. As of 2026, that's a maximum 8-year service window on the earliest units — much younger than Wolf (Sub-Zero Group since 1979), Thermador (BSH since 1947 in the US), or even Hestan's own outdoor lineup (launched 2016). We're calling out the patterns we're actually seeing on our route, not extrapolating multi-decade wear curves the equipment hasn't lived through yet. <strong>Most common current Hestan calls in our LA mix:</strong> CircuFlame burner spark electrode wear (the high-BTU center burner electrode erodes faster than surrounding zones); smart-platform connectivity drops (app pairing failures, firmware version issues); KDO wall oven TwinVection fan motor service (early-cohort units); and on the outdoor side GRSR / GRFR compressor and condenser fan service driven by Calabasas / Hidden Hills summer ambient temps. Year-by-year wear curves we'll refine as the install base ages.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>KRD freestanding dual-fuel ranges</h3>
        <p>30, 36, 48-inch dual-fuel ranges (KRD304, KRD365, KRD485GD). CircuFlame sealed center power burner (30,000 BTU), PureVection oven convection, MarquiseDisplay inset digital display in the oven handle, backlit knobs. Service tree: spark electrode ($185-$285), spark module ($265-$405), oven igniter ($245-$385), oven thermostat ($265-$405), bake / broil element ($245-$385), smart-control board ($385-$580).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>KRG freestanding gas ranges</h3>
        <p>30 and 36-inch gas-only freestanding ranges (KRG304, KRG365). Same CircuFlame burner architecture and brass-sealed burners as KRD line, gas-only construction (no electric oven element). Service items overlap with KRD on the cooktop side; oven side simpler than dual-fuel.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>KRT gas + KRTI induction rangetops</h3>
        <p>36 and 48-inch rangetops paired with KDO wall ovens in modular cooking setups (KRT365, KRT484GD, KRT485GD gas; KRTI36 induction). The induction variant adds a separate generator-board service category — failed zones, cookware detection issues. Common in newer-construction custom kitchens.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>KDO wall ovens</h3>
        <p>30-inch single and double wall ovens (KDO30) with TwinVection dual convection fans. Service items: convection fan motors, oven thermostat, bake / broil element, door hinge, control board. The dual-fan architecture is unique — slightly more service complexity than single-fan luxury convection, but more even bake when working properly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>GRFR + GRSR outdoor refrigeration</h3>
        <p>24-inch outdoor refrigerators built for ambient temps up to 110F (Hidden Hills and Calabasas pool decks routinely hit that envelope in August). GRFR24 fridge / freezer combo, GRSR24 single-zone refrigerator, GRSL24 left-hinged variant, GRWG dual-zone with wine storage. Compressor + condenser fan service is the main wear category.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>GABR / GMBR / GSBR outdoor grills</h3>
        <p>Built-in outdoor grills in 30-inch and 42-inch configurations, brass sealed burners on heavier outdoor-spec construction. Service items: igniter spark (weather-rated, harsher service window than indoor), burner valves, rotisserie motor, control panel. Calabasas and Hidden Hills outdoor kitchens dominate this category in our mix.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

