<!-- 05 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">05, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Hestan jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Hestan KRT365 36-inch gas rangetop, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Front-left CircuFlame center burner — click-click-no-light pattern on every cold start. Once the burner caught (typically third or fourth ignition attempt), it ran clean blue flame normally. Other four burners igniting first-strike. Unit was 4 years old, 2022 cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Spark electrode wear on the high-output center burner. The high-BTU center burner electrode wears faster than surrounding lower-BTU zones; we're starting to see early-cohort KRT units come back for this service item. Spark module tested clean, gas valve clean, igniter wiring clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Spark electrode replacement with OEM Hestan part (on truck — KRT-series electrodes are one of the items we stock for the dominant 36-inch configuration). Verified first-strike ignition across all five burners after install.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, 60 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Hestan KDO30 30-inch wall oven, Brentwood</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Convection bake giving visibly uneven results — cookies along the back of the rack browning two shades darker than the front. Convection fan audibly running but airflow felt weak when owner held a hand near the vent. Unit was 5 years old, 2021 cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> TwinVection rear-fan bearing wear — KDO uses dual convection fans (front + rear), and the rear unit had degraded enough to reduce its airflow contribution while the front continued running at full RPM. The asymmetric airflow is what produced the asymmetric browning. Wall ovens are a newer cohort for us on Hestan service (the lineup is younger than the rangetops in customer install volume), so this is one of the patterns we're still building data on. Front fan, igniter, thermostat, and bake element tested clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Rear TwinVection convection fan motor replacement with OEM Hestan part (ordered from Anaheim, arrived day 3). Verified even browning on test bake (sheet pan of cookies, front-to-back uniformity within visual tolerance).</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $485 total. Two visits — diagnostic + 3-day parts arrival.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Hestan GRFR24 outdoor refrigerator/freezer combo, Hidden Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Refrigerator side climbing to 48F during August heat wave (pool-deck ambient on the cabana ran 108F). Freezer drawer holding -2F normally. Owner had cleaned the condenser coil grille without resolution.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Refrigerator-side evaporator fan motor on an early-cohort GRFR in a Hidden Hills outdoor install — the duty cycle on outdoor refrigeration in inland summer ambient is significantly harder than indoor units, and the fridge-side evap fan is the first item we see come back for service on GRFR. Freezer-side evap and main compressor measured within spec; cooling system architecture intact, just the fridge-zone airflow had dropped.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Refrigerator-side evaporator fan motor replacement with OEM Hestan weather-rated part (on truck — GRFR fan motors are one of the stocked items given Calabasas / Hidden Hills demand). Verified refrigerator-side temperature recovery to 38F within 3 hours of repair.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $525 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

